Component Diagram

The component diagram represents the high-level software architecture of CookSnap â€“ Smart Recipe Recommendation System Using Grocery Images. 
It illustrates how different system components interact with each other to deliver intelligent recipe recommendation functionality based on grocery images.

Identified Components

User Interface (Web / Mobile Application)
Provides interfaces for users to upload grocery images, view detected ingredients, and see recipe recommendations, as well as for admins to access dashboards.

Image Processing Module
Handles image upload, validation, and preprocessing before ingredient detection.

Ingredient Detection Module
Uses image recognition techniques to identify grocery items from uploaded images.

Recipe Recommendation Module
Matches detected ingredients with available recipes and generates suitable recommendations.

Notification Service
Sends alerts or messages to users regarding successful uploads, recipe availability, or system responses.

Authentication Module
Manages secure login and access control for users and administrators.

Reporting Module
Generates basic usage and system performance reports for administrative monitoring.

Database
Stores user data, grocery images metadata, detected ingredients, recipes, and system logs.

These components work together to ensure accurate ingredient detection, intelligent recipe recommendation, secure access, and efficient system operation.

This component diagram highlights the modular structure of the CookSnap system and supports maintainability, scalability, and future enhancements.
